      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>it's kind of nice that you say that, but i don't know if it feels true. i just see her working so hard to keep me going, and then she goes home and stays up late worrying about me. it feels selfish to keep letting her do this. i just want her to have her life back, you know? to not have to spend every weekend worrying if i've fallen or if i've eaten. it feels like the only way for things to actually get easier for her is if i just wasn't in the way anymore.",
